results.name: Decimal expansion of Pi/32.
reference: George Boros and Victor H. Moll, Irresistible integrals, Cambridge University Press (2006), Chapter 13 A Master Formula, p. 250.
link: Vincenzo Librandi, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
formula: Also equals beta(3/2, 1/2)/16, where 'beta' is Euler's beta function.
Equals Integral_{x = 0..1} x^4*sqrt(1 - x^2) dx = Integral_{x = 0..1} x^5*sqrt(1 - x^4) dx = Integral_{x = 0..1} x^7*sqrt(1 - x^16) dx.
